About this item

  • Rechargeable Silent Mouse: Built-in rechargeable battery, no need change battery.it can be easily charged using the included USB cable. 2 hours charging, you can use it for 7-15 days. Special soundless design for the right and left buttons, Noiseless click, no worrying about disturbing others beside you, let you concentrate on work.
  • Colorful Light: 7 different color changes randomly while in use, offering soothing lighting, creating cool and fancy atmosphere for work and play.This wireless mouse Bluetooth with lights can give you more fun during office time.
  • Energy Saving: The mouse will be in sleep mode in 5 mins of inactivity. You can choose use the 2.4G wireless mouse when the mouse botton switch is on the 2.4G mode,or connect your laptop's Bluetooth to use the Bluetooth mouse, easy to switch,suitable for any occasion.
  • Portable Mouse and Operation Notice: Size About 4.4 x 2.3 x 1.1 inch,it can be easily put into your laptop bag and ultra-space saving.Slim and lightweight,durable ergonomic mouse is perfect for travel.The USB receiver is stored inside the back of the mouse.No need for a driver,Plug and Play!Automatic sleep mode and wake-up mode are installed to save energy.Pls Turn off the mouse LED light when not in use to expand the using life.
  • WIDE COMPATIBILITY: Accurate wireless bluetooth mouse with a working distance up to 10 meters (33 feet) for fast data transfer without delay or loss. Compatible with Windows XP, Vista, 7, 8, 10, 11, Windows ME, Mac OS and more. Also supports bluetooth connection, this LED wireless + bluetooth mouse is perfect for desktop, laptop, tablet, PC, Macbook, iPad and other bluetooth devices. for home, office, travel and more.

Product description

7pcs Color LED silent mouse portable mouse Ergonomic Allows you to focus more on staying on the job.not interrupting others to rest. Easily fits in your laptop bag to save more space. Very suitable for going out, traveling. The wrist will not feel uncomfortable even after prolonged use. Streamlined design, more intimate rechargeable mouse Bluetooth wireless dual-mode mouse 7pcs Color LED No need change battery.it can be easily charged using the included USB cable. 2 hours charging, you can use it for 7-15 days. The wireless mouse supports BT 5.2 and USB 2.4G dual-mode switching, and the effective transmission range can reach 10 meters. 7 different colors change randomly during use, providing soothing lighting effects, creating a cool and chic atmosphere for work and play. How are ratings calculated?
To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

  • Ashlee
    5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for laptops
    Reviewed in the United States on 22 June 2025
    Verified Purchase
    I ordered this mouse and it was delivered the next day. I got this mouse for my college laptop so I could use my laptop faster and efficiently. It connects to your computer the moment you plug it in and it's faster than my Logitech mouse. The color matches the pictures and it's very durable and light weight. The mouse is flat, smooth, and comfortable for your hand. Left/right buttons are quieter than most mouses but will still make some noise which is unavoidable with any mouse/keyboard. Just keep in mind when buying that it won't be completely silent/noise free. The middle mouse button (scroll button) clicks as loud as other mouses (also unavoidable). Storage is easy, this mouse has a feature that lets you store the USB insert on the bottom of the mouse so you don't need to worry about losing it. Charger is included as well. Overall it's exactly as described and a great value.

  • Jason Z.
    4.0 out of 5 stars Good mouse for a travel setup. I wouldn't use it for my daily driver through.
    Reviewed in the United States on 5 June 2025
    Verified Purchase
    Overall, the mouse works great. However, on BT5.2 mode, it seems to drop its connection and go to sleep after a VERY short (10 secs?) period of inactivity. Clicking a mouse button will wake it back up. But reconnecting is not instant. I can't fault the mouse for this - yet. The laptop I am using it on does not have BT5.2. So, it could be a protocol/compatibility issue. The mouse is VERY slim and somewhat short. If you have large hands like me, you will find that you have to arch your hand more than usual to use it. Not a big deal. This is just a travel laptop/mouse combo. So it works fine for me. Lastly, the RGB lighting is not exactly how it is depicted. There are not multiple colors on the mouse at the same time. It appears to be a single RGB LED inside the mouse that cycles through colors. Also, this cannot be turned off. Again, no biggee. Just different than what is pictured.

  • Xmetal
    3.0 out of 5 stars First impressions .. better than I'd expect
    Reviewed in the United States on 23 November 2023
    Verified Purchase
    Update 3: using this a bit again ... overall i like the mouse but i HAVE TO use the dongle .. .the BT does connect but even when in use (aka not going idle from inactivity) it keeps disconnecting and reconnecting over and over again no matter what device i try it with. like if its a wired mouse or even using the 2.4gnz dongle (i think i have the number correct there) ... like if someone by a computer kept plugging it in and pulling it out and plugging it in over and over again ... VERY annoying... BUT for the price (and this is also my first "low profile" mouse) ... i like it .. .just knowing the BT stinks ... i would still consider (using someone else's for this review) getting myself one.

    Update 2: I have used this enough to still consider this for myself (this one maybe a gift) ... but there is a big catch ... the bluetooth connection stinks ... I thought it was just (note: the firestick SEES this mouse instantly) my Firestick .. but even with different laptops and Linux distros ... the distros sees and "connects" right away BUT KEEPS disconnecting .. even turning the CHEAP feeling switch off and back to bluetooth doesn't help ... i plug in the dongle and forget BT and it appears "stable" like a normal usb dongle wireless mouse ... I dont NEED BT to work at this price of a mouse (if i paid say $12 or more i'd be disappointed) ... I have seen a few other reviews claiming constant bluetooth disconnects too. If you really want the BT part to work or NEED IT.. I'd AVOID this mouse

    Update: I have used this off and on and still like it for what it is (PLEASE manage expectations folks) ... I CAN see two cons

    BT mode is iffy at times ... like you think the battery is dead because it randomly disconnects and reconnects at random ... (sometimes turning it off and back to bt mode fixes it) ... at the same time that happens you use the usb dongle and realize "it is still holding a charge and just fine" without issue.

    SPEAKING of which .. no issues yet but the USB/off/BT switch is so small and cheap feeling i CAN mentally see that going over time. if it gets stuck in one mode (say usb) i am not sure if it charges even if you dont switch it to "off" .... if it still would ... ok you may lose the other mode for example BUT you can still use and charge it.

    This is my first "flat" type mouse and i wasn't sure if i'd like it or if it'd seem "gimmicky" for some reason ... I am NOT saying it's better than a "normal style/form basic mouse" but its different and a nice "change of pace"
    -------------
    I want to be clear these are first impressions only and i am not sure what i am doing with this mouse yet.... My idea was a Christmas gift, and if good enough i may pickup a second for another gift ... and possibly even a third considering the @ $6 price for myself.

    So far I have tried it with a second gen firestick and bluetooth mode ... after getting the Firestick to FINALLY see it ... sit seems to pair and unpair turning on and off fairly quickly HOWEVER the mouse does not control the cursor (even with MouseToggle) .... I have only tried the mouse with my 2018 Dell and not only did the laptop see the mouse instantly but it connected and WORKED 100% no issue. I am a Linux user by the way ... nothing extra needed at least on Linux Mint .. plug and play .. super easy. On the subject of the Firestick... this one had an OTG cable that when used with flash drives, it kept causing the Firestick to reboot itself (needing more power for said usb drives) ... I tried the mouse with the OTG Cable and this mouse's USB dongle... and the mouse now works great with the Firestick and the Firestick is NOT rebooting itself. By the way ... my Linux install on my Dell ... I was using Bluetooth mode on this mouse ... I say that to note ... the FS and BT issue with this mouse MAY be a "Fire device" issue and not with the mouse itself. Some "use a mouse with your Firestick" tutorials even use and link to this EXACT mouse.

    A mouse this cheap in price having a usb dongle OR BT for what you may want ... is a very nice touch.

    This is also my first "flatter" mouse and i wasnt sure if i'd like it. I have to say ... while I am still a fan of both form factors ... I do like this "flatter" feel to it. I mean if you have not had a mouse like this before your hand is more even or horizontal with the desk is all ... versus "cuping" the mouse, so to speak.

    I have a Rii RM105 wired mouse with RGB (not important to me like it is on this mouse) but i think the RGB maybe a little better in this mouse, looking at it. I eventually would EXPECT to have the scrollwheel issue as the Rii where after awhile it starts to scroll in the wrong direction but EVEN IF that happens with this mouse too ... the rest of the mouse (including scroll wheel clicking) would be a-ok.

    There is a nice SOFT click to mouse presses too.

    Overall I AM PROBABLY going to order more even knowing there are better quality mice out there ... sort of a "proof of concept" for my gifts (I have to see how the people that would get these would like it first) ... I would recommend this mouse so far ... just manage your expectations ... I have never had high end mice that is say $50+ .. so comparing them to that you may not be happy. I am also not a fan of discount store .. "off brand" mice that are low quality. This mouse doesn't feel "premium" but again noting for me it's still brand new ... it doesn't feel like "eww ... this is so cheap in quality" either. I don't expect this mouse to "last years" but for even a mouse you can throw in your laptop bag if you're not a touchpad fan that is cheap in price, IF it breaks ... that is another good use case for this.

    I dont want to "ham it up" but ... I like and am a fan of this mouse, so far
